public class SequenceCollection

A collection of sequences that makes its efficient to ask for all the sequences that declare a variable of a given type.

clear

public void clear()
Restores the collection to its initial state, meaning: the collection contains only the seeds given as input argument to the constructor. In other words, this method removes all the sequences from the collection, and them adds back the seeds given in the constructor call.
